- ## CyberPhysical
#CyberPhysical #Systems #Terminology 
Cyber-Physical System (CPS) is the term coined by the American foundation NSF (National Science Foundation) which takes its name from the result of equipping the physical components or objects that we usually find in our work- ing environment, computing and communication capabilities to convert them into intelligent objects that allow them to overcome the simple embedded systems based on capacity, security, scalability, adaptability, resilience and usability, being able to work together to form distributed and fully autonomous ecosystems, therefore, CPS go beyond individual objects by offering services over the internet as it refers to more complex systems composed from other systems and they are able to learn from the interactions that have with the physical world, so that they turn environments into intelligent ones [9]. - ## Protocols
#Protocols #IIoT #Industrial #AI #Smart #Manufacturing 
This study deals with the implementation of CPPS using low-cost devices in a simulated factory to control the industrial process and integrate shop-floor communications using the AMQP (Advanced Message Queuing Protocol) protocol. In an era in which most CPPS-related studies are conducted on high-level abstract models, this study describes more specific architectural frameworks in a real process.

- ## Protocols
#Protocols #IIoT #Industrial #AI #Smart #Manufacturing 
With the transmission of data via the AMQP protocol, process effectiveness and low bandwidth consumption for data transmission were achieved. In this way, the consumer obtains the results of the plants performance in real-time in a visual interface that can be accessed from anywhere in the world, and thus evaluate the quality of the plants process production. The AMQP communication structure developed, creates a reliable quality control, by means of a light and secure message routing, allowing to visualize in the history the state of each product in the process, It was able to identify the defective products, for decision making and corrective maintenance according to the respective analysis.
